</div></div>

<div class="topic base_wheretoapply">
<h2 class="topic base_wheretoapply_title" id="l84a61">Joint Labour Committees before July
2011</h2>

<p>Previously some employments were covered by agreements made by Joint Labour
Committees. Following a High Court decision Employment Regulation Orders ceased
to have statutory effect from 7 July 2011. </p>

<p>Employees who were covered by an ERO have existing contracts of employment
which govern their pay and conditions of work. If an employer <a href="../contracts_of_employment/being_asked_to_reduce_your_hours_of_work.html">reduces
an employee’s rate of pay</a> this would be a <a href="../contracts_of_employment/change_job_contract.html">change in their
contract of employment</a> and normally such changes require the employee’s
consent. </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
